import shapefile
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import math
import pycrs
import pyproj
import sys
def toCartesian(p):
    degToRad=math.pi/180
    return (math.cos(p[1]*degToRad)*math.cos(p[0]*degToRad),math.cos(p[1]*degToRad)*math.sin(p[0]*degToRad),math.sin(p[1]*degToRad))
def fromCartesian(p):
    degToRad=math.pi/180
    return (math.atan2(p[1],p[0])/degToRad,math.asin(p[2])/degToRad)
def normalize(p):
    dis=math.sqrt(p[0]*p[0]+p[1]*p[1]+p[2]*p[2])
    return (p[0]/dis,p[1]/dis,p[2]/dis)
def cross(a,b):
    return (a[1]*b[2]-a[2]*b[1],a[2]*b[0]-a[0]*b[2],a[0]*b[1]-a[1]*b[0])
def dist(a,b):
    lat1=a[1]
    lat2=b[1]
    lon1=a[0]
    lon2=b[0]
    p=math.pi/180
    a=0.5 - math.cos((lat2-lat1)*p)/2 + math.cos(lat1*p) * math.cos(lat2*p) * (1-math.cos((lon2-lon1)*p))/2 # https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27928/calculate-distance-between-two-latitude-longitude-points-haversine-formula
    return 2*math.asin(math.sqrt(a))
def nearPointGreatCircle(a,b,c): # https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1299567/how-to-calculate-distance-from-a-point-to-a-line-segment-on-a-sphere
    a1,b1,c1=map(toCartesian,(a,b,c))
    G=cross(a1,b1)
    F=cross(c1,G)
    t=normalize(cross(G,F))
    return fromCartesian(t)
def onSegment(a,b,c):
    return abs(dist(a,b)-dist(a,c)-dist(c,b))<10**-9
def segDist(a,b,c):
    t=nearPointGreatCircle(a,b,c)
    if onSegment(a,b,t):
        return dist(c,t)
    return min(dist(c,a),dist(c,b))
koordGrad=open('koordList.txt','rb').read().split(b'\n')
stanov={}
zupGrada={}
popis=open('popis2011.txt','rb').read().split(b'\n') # uzimamo koji je grad u kojoj ≈æupaniji iz popisa stanovni≈°tva; prvo smo tra≈æili te≈æinsku udaljenost gdje je te≈æina svakog grada/opƒáine bio njezin broj stanovnika, ali buduƒái da je bilo ƒçudno da se udaljenost od mora mijenja kroz vrijeme na kraju nismo koristili broj stanovnika
for x in popis:
    z=x.split(b'\t')
    if z[1]==b'':
        continue
    if z[4][:5]!=b'Vinod':
        imeGrada=z[1]+b' '+z[4]
    else:
        imeGrada=z[4]
    if ' ‚Äì '.encode() in imeGrada:
        imeGrada=imeGrada.split(' ‚Äì '.encode())[0]
    stan=int(b''.join(z[-1].split(b',')))
    stanov[imeGrada]=stan
    zupGrada[imeGrada]=z[0]
for x in koordGrad:
    z=x.split(b'\t')
    imeGrada=z[2].split(b'\r')[0]
    xCoord=float(z[1])
    yCoord=float(z[0])
    zup=zupGrada[imeGrada]
    pop=stanov[imeGrada]
sf=shapefile.Reader('eea_v_3035_100_k_coastline-poly_1995-2017_p_v03_r00.zip')
fromcrs=pycrs.load.from_file("eea_v_3035_100_k_coastline-poly_1995-2017_p_v03_r00/EEA_Coastline_20170228.prj")
fromproj=pyproj.crs.CRS.from_wkt(fromcrs.to_ogc_wkt())
tocrs=pycrs.parse.from_epsg_code(4326)
toproj=pyproj.crs.CRS.from_wkt(tocrs.to_ogc_wkt())
transformer=pyproj.Transformer.from_crs(fromproj,toproj)
print(sf)
fig,ax=plt.subplots()
hrv_obala=sf.shape(33540).points[328000:350000] # dio obale koji je relevantan za hrvatsku
minx=min([hrv_obala[i][0] for i in range(len(hrv_obala))])
maxx=max([hrv_obala[i][0] for i in range(len(hrv_obala))])
miny=min([hrv_obala[i][1] for i in range(len(hrv_obala))])
maxy=max([hrv_obala[i][1] for i in range(len(hrv_obala))])
for i in range(len(hrv_obala)):
    hrv_obala[i]=transformer.transform(hrv_obala[i][0],hrv_obala[i][1]) # pretvorimo projekciju koja se koristila u koordinate
xs=[p[0] for p in hrv_obala]
ys=[p[1] for p in hrv_obala]
ax.plot(xs,ys)
otoci=[]
for i in range(70972):
    boundingBox=sf.shape(i).bbox
    if boundingBox[0]>minx and boundingBox[1]>miny and boundingBox[2]<maxx and boundingBox[3]<maxy: # ako je otok potpuno sadr≈æan u bounding boxu hrvatske obale onda je to hrvatski otok kojeg takoƒëer treba gledati
        otok=[]
        for x in sf.shape(i).points:
            otok.append(transformer.transform(x[0],x[1]))
        xs=[p[0] for p in otok]
        ys=[p[1] for p in otok]
        ax.plot(xs,ys)
        otoci.append(otok)
plt.show()
totStanovnika={}
zbrUdalj={}
zupanije=[]
for x in koordGrad:
    z=x.split(b'\t')
    imeGrada=z[2].split(b'\r')[0]
    xCoord=float(z[1])
    yCoord=float(z[0])
    zup=zupGrada[imeGrada]
    pop=stanov[imeGrada]
    pop=1
    toc=(xCoord,yCoord)
    minDist=-1
    for i in range(len(hrv_obala)-1):
        di=segDist(hrv_obala[i],hrv_obala[i+1],toc)
        if minDist==-1 or di<minDist:
            minDist=di
    for obala_otoka in otoci:
        for i in range(len(obala_otoka)-1):
            di=segDist(obala_otoka[i],obala_otoka[i+1],toc)
        if minDist==-1 or di<minDist:
            minDist=di
    minDist*=6371 # radijus zemlje u km
    print(imeGrada,xCoord,yCoord,zup,pop,minDist)
    if zup not in zupanije:
        zupanije.append(zup)
        totStanovnika[zup]=0
        zbrUdalj[zup]=0
    totStanovnika[zup]+=pop
    zbrUdalj[zup]+=pop*minDist
ff=open('res.txt','wb')
for x in zupanije:
    prosUdalj=zbrUdalj[x]/totStanovnika[x]
    print(x,prosUdalj,totStanovnika[x])
    ff.write(x+b': '+str(prosUdalj).encode()+b'\n')
ff.close()

' Complete ECC-ELIZA Clone in FreeBASIC for DOS
' Full implementation with ELIZA.DAT parser
' Based on ECC-ELIZA V4.09 specification
' Version 4.2 - Fixed array bounds and large DAT file handling

' Constants - Updated for VERY large DAT files
Const MAX_CATEGORIES = 3500      ' Increased to handle your massive 3335+ category DAT file
Const MAX_FLAGS = 128
Const MAX_DISCUSSIONS = 128
Const MAX_LINE_LENGTH = 512
Const MAX_SUBJECT_LENGTH = 25
Const MAX_MISSING_ASTERISK = 25
Const MAX_DISCUSSION_LENGTH = 32

' Data structures
Type KeywordType
    text As String
    locked As Long  ' 1 if keyword ends with &
End Type

Type ReplyType
    text As String
    exitType As Long  ' 0=normal, 1=query(:), 2=force(;), 3=percent(%)
End Type

Type FlagCommandType
    flagNum As Long
    operation As String  ' =, +, -
    value As Long
    probability As Long
End Type

Type CategoryType
    REDIM keywords(ANY) As KeywordType     ' Dynamic array for keywords
    keywordCount As Long
    REDIM replies(ANY) As ReplyType        ' Dynamic array for replies
    replyCount As Long
    REDIM replyUsageCount(ANY) As Long     ' Dynamic array for usage counts
    subject As String
    missingAsterisk As String
    flagCommands(1 To 5) As FlagCommandType
    flagCount As Long
    ifCondition As String
    ifFlag As Long
    ifOperator As String
    ifValue As Long
    probability As Long  ' C command, default 100
    isExecute As Long  ' 1 if contains _EXE keyword
    isFixed As Long    ' 1 if fixed category (K_NAME, etc.)
End Type

Type FlagType
    value As Long
    autoChange As Long  ' For reserved flags 90-127
End Type

' Global variables - Updated array size
Dim Shared categories(1 To MAX_CATEGORIES) As CategoryType
Dim Shared categoryCount As Long
Dim Shared flags(0 To 127) As FlagType
Dim Shared discussions(1 To MAX_DISCUSSIONS) As String
Dim Shared discussionCount As Long
Dim Shared userName As String
Dim Shared replyHistory(1 To 1000) As String
Dim Shared replyHistoryCount As Long
Dim Shared subjects(1 To 100) As String
Dim Shared subjectCount As Long
Dim Shared inputHistory(1 To 100) As String
Dim Shared inputHistoryCount As Long
Dim Shared blankCount As Long
Dim Shared repeatCount As Long
Dim Shared conversationCount As Long
Dim Shared lastInput As String
Dim Shared currentReplyIndex(1 To MAX_CATEGORIES) As Long

' String utility functions

' Replace all occurrences of oldStr with newStr in text
Function StringReplace(text As String, oldStr As String, newStr As String) As String
    Dim result As String = text
    Dim position As Long = 1
    Dim oldLen As Long = Len(oldStr)
    Dim newLen As Long = Len(newStr)
    
    If oldLen = 0 Then Return result
    
    Do
        position = InStr(position, result, oldStr)
        If position = 0 Then Exit Do
        
        result = Left(result, position - 1) + newStr + Mid(result, position + oldLen)
        position = position + newLen
    Loop
    
    Return result
End Function

' Split string by delimiter into array - Fixed for 0-based arrays
Sub StringSplit(text As String, delimiter As String, parts() As String, ByRef partCount As Long)
    Dim tempText As String = text
    Dim position As Long
    partCount = 0
    
    If Len(delimiter) = 0 Then
        partCount = 1
        ReDim parts(0 To 0)  ' 0-based
        parts(0) = text      ' 0-based index
        Exit Sub
    End If
    
    ' Count parts first
    Do
        position = InStr(tempText, delimiter)
        If position = 0 Then
            partCount += 1
            Exit Do
        End If
        partCount += 1
        tempText = Mid(tempText, position + Len(delimiter))
    Loop
    
    ' Allocate array (0-based)
    ReDim parts(0 To partCount - 1)
    
    ' Fill array
    tempText = text
    Dim i As Long = 0  ' Start at 0
    Do
        position = InStr(tempText, delimiter)
        If position = 0 Then
            parts(i) = tempText
            Exit Do
        End If
        parts(i) = Left(tempText, position - 1)
        tempText = Mid(tempText, position + Len(delimiter))
        i += 1
    Loop
End Sub

' Trim whitespace from both ends
Function StringTrim(text As String) As String
    Dim result As String = text
    Dim i As Long
    
    ' Trim left
    For i = 1 To Len(result)
        If Mid(result, i, 1) <> " " And Mid(result, i, 1) <> Chr(9) Then Exit For
    Next i
    If i > Len(result) Then Return ""
    result = Mid(result, i)
    
    ' Trim right
    For i = Len(result) To 1 Step -1
        If Mid(result, i, 1) <> " " And Mid(result, i, 1) <> Chr(9) Then Exit For
    Next i
    result = Left(result, i)
    
    Return result
End Function

' Convert string to uppercase
Function StringUpper(text As String) As String
    Dim result As String = ""
    Dim i As Long
    
    For i = 1 To Len(text)
        Dim c As String = Mid(text, i, 1)
        If c >= "a" And c <= "z" Then
            result += Chr(Asc(c) - 32)
        Else
            result += c
        End If
    Next i
    
    Return result
End Function

' Check if string starts with prefix
Function StringStartsWith(text As String, prefix As String) As Long
    If Len(prefix) > Len(text) Then Return 0
    Return IIf(Left(text, Len(prefix)) = prefix, 1, 0)
End Function

' Check if string ends with suffix
Function StringEndsWith(text As String, suffix As String) As Long
    If Len(suffix) > Len(text) Then Return 0
    Return IIf(Right(text, Len(suffix)) = suffix, 1, 0)
End Function

' Get weekday number (1=Sunday, 2=Monday, etc.)
Function GetWeekday(dateStr As String) As Long
    Dim currentDate As String = Date
    Dim dayOfWeek As Long
    
    ' Extract day, month, year from MM-DD-YYYY or DD-MM-YYYY format
    Dim dateParts() As String
    Dim partCount As Long
    StringSplit(currentDate, "-", dateParts(), partCount)
    
    If partCount >= 3 Then
        ' Use a simple algorithm to estimate day of week
        dayOfWeek = (Val(dateParts(2)) Mod 7) + 1
    Else
        dayOfWeek = 1  ' Default to Sunday
    End If
    
    Return dayOfWeek
End Function

' Format number with leading zeros
Function FormatNumber(num As Long, digits As Long) As String
    Dim result As String = Str(num)
    result = StringTrim(result)  ' Remove leading space from Str()
    
    While Len(result) < digits
        result = "0" + result
    Wend
    
    Return result
End Function

' Helper function to debug category information
Sub DebugCategory(catIndex As Long)
    If catIndex < 1 Or catIndex > categoryCount Then
        Print "Invalid category index: " & catIndex
        Exit Sub
    End If
    
    Print "Category " & catIndex & ":"
    Print "  Keywords (" & categories(catIndex).keywordCount & "):"
    Dim i As Long
    For i = 0 To categories(catIndex).keywordCount - 1
        Print "    " & i & ": '" & categories(catIndex).keywords(i).text & "'" & IIf(categories(catIndex).keywords(i).locked, " (LOCKED)", "")
    Next i
    Print "  Replies (" & categories(catIndex).replyCount & "):"
    For i = 0 To categories(catIndex).replyCount - 1
        Print "    " & i & ": '" & Left(categories(catIndex).replies(i).text, 50) & "'"
    Next i
    Print "  Probability: " & categories(catIndex).probability
    Print "  isExecute: " & categories(catIndex).isExecute
    Print "  isFixed: " & categories(catIndex).isFixed
    Print "  Subject: '" & categories(catIndex).subject & "'"
    If categories(catIndex).ifCondition <> "" Then
        Print "  Condition: " & categories(catIndex).ifCondition
    End If
    Print
End Sub

' Test function to help debug the parsing
Sub TestFirstCategories()
    Print "Testing first 10 categories:"
    Dim i As Long
    For i = 1 To 10
        If i <= categoryCount Then
            DebugCategory(i)
        End If
    Next i
End Sub

' Function to count categories in DAT file before loading
Function CountCategoriesInFile(filename As String) As Long
    Dim fileNum As Long = FreeFile
    Dim lineData As String
    Dim categoryCount As Long = 0
    
    On Error GoTo CountError
    Open filename For Input As #fileNum
    
    Print "Scanning "; filename; " to count categories..."
    
    Do While Not EOF(fileNum)
        Line Input #fileNum, lineData
        Dim trimmedLine As String = StringTrim(lineData)
        
        ' Count K commands (keywords start new categories)
        If StringStartsWith(trimmedLine, "K ") And Len(trimmedLine) > 2 Then
            categoryCount += 1
            If categoryCount Mod 25 = 0 Then Print "Found " & categoryCount & " categories so far..."
        End If
    Loop
    
    Close #fileNum
    Print "Total categories found: " & categoryCount
    Return categoryCount
    
CountError:
    Print "Error counting categories in file"
    If fileNum > 0 Then Close #fileNum
    Return -1
End Function

' Initialize all systems
Sub InitializeSystem()
    Dim i As Long, j As Long
    
    Print "DEBUG: Initializing system..."
    
    ' Initialize flags
    For i = 0 To 127
        flags(i).value = 0
        flags(i).autoChange = 0
    Next i
    
    ' Set auto-change types for reserved flags
    For i = 90 To 99
        flags(i).autoChange = 1  ' +1 each reply
    Next i
    For i = 100 To 109
        flags(i).autoChange = -1  ' -1 each reply
    Next i
    For i = 110 To 119
        flags(i).autoChange = 2  ' +2 each reply
    Next i
    For i = 120 To 127
        flags(i).autoChange = -2  ' -2 each reply
    Next i
    
    Print "DEBUG: Initializing categories..."
    
    ' Initialize categories with error handling
    For i = 1 To MAX_CATEGORIES
        categories(i).keywordCount = 0
        categories(i).replyCount = 0
        categories(i).flagCount = 0
        categories(i).probability = 100
        categories(i).isExecute = 0
        categories(i).isFixed = 0
        categories(i).subject = ""
        categories(i).missingAsterisk = ""
        categories(i).ifCondition = ""
        categories(i).ifFlag = 0
        categories(i).ifOperator = ""
        categories(i).ifValue = 0
        currentReplyIndex(i) = 0
        
        ' Initialize dynamic arrays with proper initial size
        On Error GoTo InitError
        with categories(i)
        ReDim .keywords(0 To 9)        ' Start with space for 10 keywords (0-9)
        ReDim .replies(0 To 9)         ' Start with space for 10 replies (0-9)
        ReDim .replyUsageCount(0 To 9) ' Usage counts for replies (0-9)
        
        ' Initialize all array elements
        For j = 0 To 9
            .keywords(j).text = ""
            .keywords(j).locked = 0
            .replies(j).text = ""
            .replies(j).exitType = 0
            .replyUsageCount(j) = 0
        Next j
        end with
        On Error GoTo 0
        
        ' Progress indicator for large initialization - more frequent for massive arrays
        If i Mod 50 = 0 Then Print "DEBUG: Initialized " & i & " of " & MAX_CATEGORIES & " categories..."
    Next i
    
    ' Initialize counters
    categoryCount = 0
    discussionCount = 0
    replyHistoryCount = 0
    subjectCount = 0
    inputHistoryCount = 0
    blankCount = 0
    repeatCount = 0
    conversationCount = 0
    lastInput = ""
    userName = ""
    
    Randomize Timer
    
    Print "DEBUG: System initialization complete"
    Exit Sub
    
InitError:
    Print "FATAL ERROR: Cannot initialize category " & i
    ' Print "Error: " & Err & " - " & Error
    End
End Sub

' Get current time description
Function GetTimeDescription() As String
    Dim timeStr As String = Time
    Dim dateStr As String = Date
    Dim h As Long = Val(Left(timeStr, 2))
    Dim dayOfWeek As Long = GetWeekday(dateStr)
    Dim dayName As String
    Dim timeOfDay As String
    
    ' Get day name
    Select Case dayOfWeek
        Case 1: dayName = "SUNDAY"
        Case 2: dayName = "MONDAY" 
        Case 3: dayName = "TUESDAY"
        Case 4: dayName = "WEDNESDAY"
        Case 5: dayName = "THURSDAY"
        Case 6: dayName = "FRIDAY"
        Case 7: dayName = "SATURDAY"
    End Select
    
    ' Get time of day
    If h >= 5 And h < 12 Then
        timeOfDay = "MORNING"
    ElseIf h >= 12 And h < 17 Then
        timeOfDay = "AFTERNOON"
    ElseIf h >= 17 And h < 21 Then
        timeOfDay = "EVENING"
    Else
        timeOfDay = "NIGHT"
    End If
    
    ' Check for weekend
    If dayOfWeek = 1 Or dayOfWeek = 7 Then
        Return "WEEKEND " + timeOfDay
    Else
        Return dayName + " " + timeOfDay
    End If
End Function

' Enhanced input cleaning for better keyword matching
Function CleanInput(text As String) As String
    Dim result As String = StringTrim(text)
    Dim i As Long
    
    ' Convert to uppercase
    result = StringUpper(result)
    
    ' Replace contractions and common variations
    result = StringReplace(result, "WON'T", "WILL NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "CAN'T", "CAN NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "DON'T", "DO NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "DIDN'T", "DID NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "SHOULDN'T", "SHOULD NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "WOULDN'T", "WOULD NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "COULDN'T", "COULD NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "HAVEN'T", "HAVE NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "HASN'T", "HAS NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "HADN'T", "HAD NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "ISN'T", "IS NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "AREN'T", "ARE NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "WASN'T", "WAS NOT")
    result = StringReplace(result, "WEREN'T", "WERE NOT")
    
    ' Replace special characters
    result = StringReplace(result, "`", "'")
    result = StringReplace(result, Chr(9), " ")  ' Tab to space
    
    ' Normalize punctuation - ensure spaces around punctuation
    For i = Len(result) To 1 Step -1
        Dim c As String = Mid(result, i, 1)
        If c = "." Or c = "," Or c = "!" Or c = "?" Or c = ";" Or c = ":" Then
            ' Add space before punctuation if needed
            If i > 1 And Mid(result, i-1, 1) <> " " Then
                result = Left(result, i-1) + " " + Mid(result, i)
                i += 1  ' Adjust for inserted space
            End If
            ' Add space after punctuation if needed
            If i < Len(result) And Mid(result, i+1, 1) <> " " Then
                result = Left(result, i) + " " + Mid(result, i+1)
            End If
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' Remove multiple spaces
    Do While InStr(result, "  ") > 0
        result = StringReplace(result, "  ", " ")
    Loop
    
    Return StringTrim(result)
End Function

' Comprehensive pronoun reversal system
Function ReversePronouns(text As String) As String
    Dim result As String = " " + StringUpper(text) + " "
    
    ' Use temporary markers to avoid double replacement
    ' Primary pronoun reversals
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU ARE ", " ~IAMTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I AM ", " ~YOUARETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~IAMTEMP~ ", " I AM ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOUARETEMP~ ", " YOU ARE ")
    
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU WERE ", " ~IWERETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I WAS ", " ~YOUWERETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I WERE ", " ~YOUWERETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~IWERETEMP~ ", " I WAS ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOUWERETEMP~ ", " YOU WERE ")
    
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOUR ", " ~MYTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " MY ", " ~YOURTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~MYTEMP~ ", " MY ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOURTEMP~ ", " YOUR ")
    
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOURS ", " ~MINETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " MINE ", " ~YOURSTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~MINETEMP~ ", " MINE ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOURSTEMP~ ", " YOURS ")
    
    ' Contractions
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU'RE ", " ~IMTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I'M ", " ~YOURETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~IMTEMP~ ", " I'M ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOURETEMP~ ", " YOU'RE ")
    
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU'VE ", " ~IVETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I'VE ", " ~YOUVETEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~IVETEMP~ ", " I'VE ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOUVETEMP~ ", " YOU'VE ")
    
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU'LL ", " ~ILLTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I'LL ", " ~YOULLTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~ILLTEMP~ ", " I'LL ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOULLTEMP~ ", " YOU'LL ")
    
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU'D ", " ~IDTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " I'D ", " ~YOUDTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~IDTEMP~ ", " I'D ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOUDTEMP~ ", " YOU'D ")
    
    ' Simple pronouns
    result = StringReplace(result, " ME ", " ~YOUTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOUTEMP~ ", " YOU ")
    
    ' Handle remaining YOU -> I
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOU ", " I ")
    
    ' Self references
    result = StringReplace(result, " MYSELF ", " ~YOURSELFTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " YOURSELF ", " ~MYSELFTEMP~ ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~YOURSELFTEMP~ ", " YOURSELF ")
    result = StringReplace(result, " ~MYSELFTEMP~ ", " MYSELF ")
    
    Return StringTrim(result)
End Function

' Extract text after keyword for * parameter
Function ExtractAsteriskText(userInput As String, keyword As String) As String
    Dim inputCleaned As String = " " + CleanInput(userInput) + " "
    Dim cleanKeyword As String = " " + StringUpper(keyword) + " "
    
    Dim position As Long = InStr(inputCleaned, cleanKeyword)
    If position = 0 Then Return ""
    
    Dim afterKeyword As String = Mid(inputCleaned, position + Len(cleanKeyword))
    afterKeyword = StringTrim(afterKeyword)
    
    ' Define breaking words
    Dim breakWords(1 To 12) As String
    breakWords(1) = "AND"
    breakWords(2) = "BUT"
    breakWords(3) = "IF"
    breakWords(4) = "WHEN"
    breakWords(5) = "BECAUSE"
    breakWords(6) = "SINCE"
    breakWords(7) = "WHILE"
    breakWords(8) = "ALTHOUGH"
    breakWords(9) = "UNLESS"
    breakWords(10) = "UNTIL"
    breakWords(11) = "BEFORE"
    breakWords(12) = "AFTER"
    
    Dim result As String = afterKeyword
    Dim i As Long
    
    ' Check for punctuation
    For i = 1 To Len(result)
        Dim c As String = Mid(result, i, 1)
        If c = "." Or c = "," Or c = "!" Or c = "?" Or c = ";" Or c = ":" Then
            result = StringTrim(Left(result, i - 1))
            Exit For
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' Check for breaking words
    For i = 1 To 12
        Dim checkStr As String = " " + StringUpper(result) + " "
        Dim breakWord As String = " " + breakWords(i) + " "
        Dim pos2 As Long = InStr(checkStr, breakWord)
        If pos2 > 0 Then
            result = StringTrim(Left(result, pos2 - 1))
            Exit For
        End If
    Next i
    
    If result <> "" Then
        Return ReversePronouns(result)
    Else
        Return ""
    End If
End Function

' Extract first word after keyword for _ parameter
Function ExtractUnderscoreText(userInput As String, keyword As String) As String
    Dim asteriskText As String = ExtractAsteriskText(userInput, keyword)
    If asteriskText = "" Then Return ""
    
    Dim spacePos As Long = InStr(asteriskText, " ")
    If spacePos > 0 Then
        Return Left(asteriskText, spacePos - 1)
    Else
        Return asteriskText
    End If
End Function

' Process reply text with all parameter substitutions
Function ProcessReply(reply As String, userInput As String, keyword As String, missingAsterisk As String) As String
    Dim result As String = reply
    
    ' Handle exit types first
    If StringStartsWith(result, ":") Then
        result = Mid(result, 2)
        ' Will handle exit query after processing
    ElseIf StringStartsWith(result, ";") Then
        result = Mid(result, 2)
        ' Will handle forced exit after processing
    End If
    
    ' Replace basic parameters
    result = StringReplace(result, "|", userName)
    result = StringReplace(result, "^", GetTimeDescription())
    
    ' Handle keyword substitution with pronoun reversal
    If InStr(result, "\") > 0 Then
        result = StringReplace(result, "\", ReversePronouns(keyword))
    End If
    
    ' Handle discussion subjects (@)
    If InStr(result, "@") > 0 And discussionCount > 0 Then
        Dim randDiscussion As Long = Int(Rnd * discussionCount) + 1
        ' Validate index is in bounds
        If randDiscussion >= 1 And randDiscussion <= discussionCount And randDiscussion <= MAX_DISCUSSIONS Then
            result = StringReplace(result, "@", discussions(randDiscussion))
        Else
            result = StringReplace(result, "@", "something")  ' Safe fallback
        End If
    End If
    
    ' Handle previous subjects (~) - simplified
    If InStr(result, "~") > 0 And subjectCount > 0 Then
        Dim randSubject As Long = Int(Rnd * subjectCount) + 1
        ' Validate index is in bounds
        If randSubject >= 1 And randSubject <= subjectCount And randSubject <= 100 Then
            result = StringReplace(result, "~", subjects(randSubject))
        Else
            result = StringReplace(result, "~", "that")  ' Safe fallback
        End If
    End If
    
    ' Handle * parameter
    If InStr(result, "*") > 0 Then
        Dim asteriskText As String = ExtractAsteriskText(userInput, keyword)
        If asteriskText = "" And missingAsterisk <> "" Then
            asteriskText = missingAsterisk
        End If
        result = StringReplace(result, "*", asteriskText)
    End If
    
    ' Handle _ parameter  
    If InStr(result, "_") > 0 Then
        Dim underscoreText As String = ExtractUnderscoreText(userInput, keyword)
        If underscoreText = "" And missingAsterisk <> "" Then
            underscoreText = missingAsterisk
        End If
        result = StringReplace(result, "_", underscoreText)
    End If
    
    ' Handle version parameter (ASCII 200)
    result = StringReplace(result, Chr(200), "4.09")
    
    Return result
End Function

' Improved keyword matching function
Function KeywordMatches(keyword As KeywordType, userInput As String) As Long
    Dim inputCleaned As String = CleanInput(userInput)
    Dim keywordText As String = StringUpper(keyword.text)
    
    ' Handle locked keywords (ending with &)
    If keyword.locked Then
        ' Locked keyword - exact match only (ignoring punctuation and spaces)
        Dim stripped As String = ""
        Dim keywordStripped As String = ""
        Dim i As Long
        
        ' Remove all non-alphanumeric characters from input
        For i = 1 To Len(inputCleaned)
            Dim c As String = Mid(inputCleaned, i, 1)
            If (c >= "A" And c <= "Z") Or (c >= "0" And c <= "9") Then
                stripped += c
            End If
        Next i
        
        ' Remove all non-alphanumeric characters from keyword
        For i = 1 To Len(keywordText)
            Dim c As String = Mid(keywordText, i, 1)
            If (c >= "A" And c <= "Z") Or (c >= "0" And c <= "9") Then
                keywordStripped += c
            End If
        Next i
        
        Return IIf(stripped = keywordStripped, 1, 0)
    Else
        ' Normal keyword - must match as complete words with word boundaries
        Dim searchInput As String = " " + inputCleaned + " "
        Dim searchKeyword As String = " " + keywordText + " "
        
        Return IIf(InStr(searchInput, searchKeyword) > 0, 1, 0)
    End If
End Function

' Execute flag commands
Sub ExecuteFlagCommands(catIndex As Long)
    Dim i As Long
    For i = 1 To categories(catIndex).flagCount
        Dim cmd As FlagCommandType = categories(catIndex).flagCommands(i)
        
        If cmd.flagNum < 0 Or cmd.flagNum > 127 Then Continue For
        If Int(Rnd * 100) + 1 > cmd.probability Then Continue For
        
        Select Case cmd.operation
            Case "="
                flags(cmd.flagNum).value = cmd.value
            Case "+"
                flags(cmd.flagNum).value += cmd.value
            Case "-"
                flags(cmd.flagNum).value -= cmd.value
        End Select
        
        ' Clamp values
        If flags(cmd.flagNum).value > 128 Then flags(cmd.flagNum).value = 128
        If flags(cmd.flagNum).value < -127 Then flags(cmd.flagNum).value = -127
    Next i
End Sub

' Update reserved flags after each reply
Sub UpdateReservedFlags()
    Dim i As Long
    For i = 0 To 127
        If flags(i).autoChange <> 0 Then
            flags(i).value += flags(i).autoChange
            If flags(i).value > 128 Then flags(i).value = 128
            If flags(i).value < -127 Then flags(i).value = -127
        End If
    Next i
End Sub

' Get next reply from category using rotation system
Function GetNextReply(catIndex As Long) As Long
    Dim i As Long
    Dim minUsage As Long = 999999
    Dim replyIndex As Long = 0
    
    ' Find minimum usage count - using 0-based arrays
    For i = 0 To categories(catIndex).replyCount - 1
        If categories(catIndex).replyUsageCount(i) < minUsage Then
            minUsage = categories(catIndex).replyUsageCount(i)
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' Find all replies with minimum usage - use dynamic array
    Dim candidateCount As Long = 0
    ' Create a dynamic array sized to the actual reply count (using 0-based)
    ReDim candidates(0 To categories(catIndex).replyCount - 1) As Long
    
    For i = 0 To categories(catIndex).replyCount - 1
        If categories(catIndex).replyUsageCount(i) = minUsage Then
            candidates(candidateCount) = i
            candidateCount += 1
        End If
    Next i

    ' Pick random candidate
    If candidateCount > 0 Then
        Dim randomIndex As Long = Int(Rnd * candidateCount)
        ' Make sure the random index is in bounds
        If randomIndex >= 0 And randomIndex < candidateCount Then
            replyIndex = candidates(randomIndex)
            ' Make sure the reply index is valid before incrementing usage count
            If replyIndex >= 0 And replyIndex < categories(catIndex).replyCount Then
                categories(catIndex).replyUsageCount(replyIndex) += 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    
    ' Safety check before returning replyIndex
    If replyIndex < 0 Or replyIndex >= categories(catIndex).replyCount Then
        replyIndex = 0  ' Set to first reply as fallback
    End If
    
    Return replyIndex
End Function

' Check for improper input patterns
Function IsImproperInput(userInput As String) As Long
    Dim cleaned As String = CleanInput(userInput)
    Dim i As Long
    Dim letterCount As Long = 0
    Dim punctCount As Long = 0
    Dim repeatChar As Long = 0
    
    ' Count characters
    For i = 1 To Len(cleaned)
        Dim c As String = Mid(cleaned, i, 1)
        If c >= "A" And c <= "Z" Then
            letterCount += 1
        ElseIf c = "!" Or c = "?" Or c = "." Then
            punctCount += 1
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' Check for excessive punctuation
    If punctCount > letterCount Then Return 1
    
    ' Check for character repetition (like "aaaaaa")
    For i = 1 To Len(cleaned) - 2
        If Mid(cleaned, i, 1) = Mid(cleaned, i+1, 1) And Mid(cleaned, i, 1) = Mid(cleaned, i+2, 1) Then
            repeatChar += 1
            If repeatChar > 2 Then Return 1
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' Check for random character patterns
    If letterCount > 0 And (punctCount * 100 / letterCount) > 50 Then Return 1
    
    Return 0
End Function

' Detect input repetition
Function IsRepeatedInput(userInput As String) As Long
    Return IIf(StringUpper(StringTrim(userInput)) = StringUpper(StringTrim(lastInput)), 1, 0)
End Function

' Process fixed categories
Function ProcessFixedCategory(categoryName As String) As String
    Dim i As Long, j As Long
    For i = 1 To categoryCount
        For j = 0 To categories(i).keywordCount - 1
            If categories(i).keywords(j).text = categoryName Then
                ExecuteFlagCommands(i)
                Dim replyIndex As Long = GetNextReply(i)
                Dim replyText As String = categories(i).replies(replyIndex).text
                Dim response As String = ProcessReply(replyText, "", categoryName, categories(i).missingAsterisk)
                UpdateReservedFlags()
                Return response
            End If
        Next j
    Next i
    
    ' Fallback responses for missing fixed categories
    Select Case categoryName
        Case "K_BLANK"
            Return "PLEASE WRITE SOMETHING, " + userName
        Case "K_REPEAT"
            Return "DON'T REPEAT YOURSELF PLEASE"
        Case "K_IMPRP"
            Return "PLEASE TYPE IN PROPER ENGLISH"
        Case "K_SHORT"
            Return "PLEASE TYPE LONGER SENTENCES"
        Case "K_LONG"
            Return "PLEASE BE MORE CONCISE"
        Case "K_NAME"
            Return "ENTER YOUR FIRST NAME PLEASE:"
        Case "K_HELLO"
            Return "HELLO " + userName + ", I AM YOUR COMPUTERIZED PSYCHOLOGIST."
        Case "K_NORMQ"
            Return "GOODBYE " + userName + "! HAVE A NICE DAY!"
        Case Else
            Return "PLEASE CONTINUE"
    End Select
End Function

' Improved ParseDataLine with better handling for complex ELIZA.DAT
Sub ParseDataLine(lineData As String, ByRef currentCategory As Long, ByRef currentProbability As Long)
    Dim trimmedLine As String = StringTrim(lineData)
    If trimmedLine = "" Or StringStartsWith(trimmedLine, "#") Then Exit Sub
    
    Dim commandChar As String = Left(trimmedLine, 1)
    Dim content As String = StringTrim(Mid(trimmedLine, 2))
    
    Select Case commandChar
        Case "K"  ' Keyword
            If content <> "" Then
                ' Check if this starts a new category or adds to existing
                Dim isNewCategory As Long = 0
                
                ' Determine if this should start a new category
                ' New category if: no current category, or previous category already has replies
                If currentCategory = 0 Then
                    isNewCategory = 1
                ElseIf currentCategory > 0 And currentCategory <= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                    If categories(currentCategory).replyCount > 0 Then
                        isNewCategory = 1
                    End If
                End If
                
                If isNewCategory Then
                    ' Start new category
                    If currentCategory >= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                        Print "ERROR: Reached maximum category limit of " & MAX_CATEGORIES
                        Exit Sub
                    End If
                    
                    currentCategory += 1
                    categoryCount = currentCategory
                    
                    ' Progress indicator
                    If currentCategory Mod 50 = 0 Then 
                        Print "Loading category " & currentCategory & "..."
                    End If
                    
                    ' Initialize the new category
                    categories(currentCategory).keywordCount = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).replyCount = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).flagCount = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).probability = currentProbability
                    categories(currentCategory).isExecute = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).isFixed = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).subject = ""
                    categories(currentCategory).missingAsterisk = ""
                    categories(currentCategory).ifCondition = ""
                    categories(currentCategory).ifFlag = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).ifOperator = ""
                    categories(currentCategory).ifValue = 0
                End If
                
                ' Add keyword to current category
                If currentCategory > 0 And currentCategory <= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                    Dim keyIndex As Long = categories(currentCategory).keywordCount
                    
                    ' Check if we need to grow the keywords array
                    If keyIndex > UBound(categories(currentCategory).keywords) Then
                        Dim currentSize As Long = UBound(categories(currentCategory).keywords) + 1
                        Dim newSize As Long = currentSize + 10
                        
                        On Error GoTo KeywordResizeError
                        with categories(currentCategory)
                        ReDim Preserve .keywords(0 To newSize - 1)
                        end with
                        On Error GoTo 0
                        
                        ' Initialize new entries
                        Dim i As Long
                        For i = keyIndex To newSize - 1
                            categories(currentCategory).keywords(i).text = ""
                            categories(currentCategory).keywords(i).locked = 0
                        Next i
                    End If
                    
                    ' Check for locked keyword (&)
                    If StringEndsWith(content, "&") Then
                        categories(currentCategory).keywords(keyIndex).text = Left(content, Len(content) - 1)
                        categories(currentCategory).keywords(keyIndex).locked = 1
                    Else
                        categories(currentCategory).keywords(keyIndex).text = content
                        categories(currentCategory).keywords(keyIndex).locked = 0
                    End If
                    
                    categories(currentCategory).keywordCount += 1
                    
                    ' Check for special keywords
                    If content = "_EXE" Then
                        categories(currentCategory).isExecute = 1
                    ElseIf StringStartsWith(content, "K_") Then
                        categories(currentCategory).isFixed = 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            
        Case "R"  ' Reply
            If currentCategory <= 0 Or currentCategory > MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                Exit Sub
            End If
            
            If content <> "" Then
                Dim replyIndex As Long = categories(currentCategory).replyCount
                
                ' Check if we need to grow the replies arrays
                If replyIndex > UBound(categories(currentCategory).replies) Then
                    Dim currentSize As Long = UBound(categories(currentCategory).replies) + 1
                    Dim newSize As Long = currentSize + 20
                    
                    On Error GoTo ReplyResizeError
                    with categories(currentCategory)
                    ReDim Preserve .replies(0 To newSize - 1)
                    ReDim Preserve .replyUsageCount(0 To newSize - 1)
                    end with
                    On Error GoTo 0
                    
                    ' Initialize new entries
                    Dim i As Long
                    For i = replyIndex To newSize - 1
                        categories(currentCategory).replyUsageCount(i) = 0
                    Next i
                End If
                
                ' Add the reply
                If replyIndex >= 0 And replyIndex <= UBound(categories(currentCategory).replies) Then
                    ' Check for exit types
                    If StringStartsWith(content, ":") Then
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).exitType = 1
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).text = Mid(content, 2)
                    ElseIf StringStartsWith(content, ";") Then
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).exitType = 2
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).text = Mid(content, 2)
                    ElseIf content = "%" Then
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).exitType = 3
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).text = "%"
                    Else
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).exitType = 0
                        categories(currentCategory).replies(replyIndex).text = content
                    End If
                    
                    categories(currentCategory).replyUsageCount(replyIndex) = 0
                    categories(currentCategory).replyCount += 1
                End If
            End If
            
        Case "C"  ' Probability
            Dim probValue As Long = Val(content)
            If probValue < 0 Then probValue = 0
            If probValue > 100 Then probValue = 100
            currentProbability = probValue
            
            ' Apply to current category if it exists and has no replies yet
            If currentCategory > 0 And currentCategory <= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                If categories(currentCategory).replyCount = 0 Then
                    categories(currentCategory).probability = currentProbability
                End If
            End If
            
        Case "F"  ' Flag command
            If currentCategory <= 0 Or currentCategory > MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                Exit Sub
            End If
            
            If categories(currentCategory).flagCount < 5 Then
                categories(currentCategory).flagCount += 1
                Dim flagIndex As Long = categories(currentCategory).flagCount
                
                ' Parse F command: flagNum,operation,value,probability
                Dim parts() As String
                Dim partCount As Long
                StringSplit(content, ",", parts(), partCount)
                
                If partCount >= 4 And flagIndex >= 1 And flagIndex <= 5 Then
                    categories(currentCategory).flagCommands(flagIndex).flagNum = Val(parts(0))
                    categories(currentCategory).flagCommands(flagIndex).operation = StringTrim(parts(1))
                    categories(currentCategory).flagCommands(flagIndex).value = Val(parts(2))
                    categories(currentCategory).flagCommands(flagIndex).probability = Val(parts(3))
                End If
            End If
            
        Case "I"  ' If condition
            If currentCategory > 0 And currentCategory <= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                categories(currentCategory).ifCondition = content
                
                ' Parse I condition: flagNum,operator,value
                Dim parts() As String
                Dim partCount As Long
                StringSplit(content, ",", parts(), partCount)
                
                If partCount >= 3 Then
                    categories(currentCategory).ifFlag = Val(parts(0))
                    categories(currentCategory).ifOperator = StringTrim(parts(1))
                    categories(currentCategory).ifValue = Val(parts(2))
                End If
            End If
            
        Case "G"  ' Grant (set initial flag value)
            ' Parse G command: flagNum,value
            Dim parts() As String
            Dim partCount As Long
            StringSplit(content, ",", parts(), partCount)
            
            If partCount >= 2 Then
                Dim flagNum As Long = Val(parts(0))
                Dim flagValue As Long = Val(parts(1))
                If flagNum >= 0 And flagNum <= 127 Then
                    flags(flagNum).value = flagValue
                End If
            End If
            
        Case "S"  ' Subject
            If currentCategory > 0 And currentCategory <= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                categories(currentCategory).subject = Left(content, MAX_SUBJECT_LENGTH)
            End If
            
        Case "M"  ' Missing asterisk
            If currentCategory > 0 And currentCategory <= MAX_CATEGORIES Then
                categories(currentCategory).missingAsterisk = Left(content, MAX_MISSING_ASTERISK)
            End If
            
        Case "D"  ' Discussion subject
            If discussionCount < MAX_DISCUSSIONS Then
                discussionCount += 1
                discussions(discussionCount) = Left(content, MAX_DISCUSSION_LENGTH)
            End If
    End Select
    
    Exit Sub
    
KeywordResizeError:
    Print "ERROR: Cannot resize keyword array for category " & currentCategory
    'Resume Next
    
ReplyResizeError:
    Print "ERROR: Cannot resize reply array for category " & currentCategory
    'Resume Next
End Sub


' Updated LoadDataFile function - Fixed return logic
Function LoadDataFile(filename As String) As Long
    ' First, count how many categories the file has
    Dim actualCategoryCount As Long = CountCategoriesInFile(filename)
    
    If actualCategoryCount = -1 Then
        Print "ERROR: Cannot read file " & filename
        Return 0
    End If
    
    If actualCategoryCount > MAX_CATEGORIES Then
        Print "WARNING: This DAT file has " & actualCategoryCount & " categories"
        Print "WARNING: But the program limit is " & MAX_CATEGORIES
        Print "WARNING: Only the first " & MAX_CATEGORIES & " categories will be loaded"
        Print "WARNING: Consider increasing MAX_CATEGORIES and recompiling"
        Print ""
    End If
    
    Dim fileNum As Long = FreeFile
    Dim lineData As String
    Dim currentCategory As Long = 0
    Dim currentProbability As Long = 100
    
    On Error GoTo ErrorHandler
    Open filename For Input As #fileNum
    
    Print "Loading data file: "; filename
    
    ' Parse file line by line
    Do While Not EOF(fileNum)
        Line Input #fileNum, lineData
        ParseDataLine(lineData, currentCategory, currentProbability)
        
        ' Stop if we've hit the limit
        If currentCategory >= MAX_CATEGORIES Then Exit Do
    Loop
    
    Close #fileNum
    
    ' Check if we actually loaded any categories
    If categoryCount = 0 Then
        Print "WARNING: No valid categories found in " & filename
        Return 0
    End If
    
    Print "Successfully loaded "; categoryCount; " categories with "; discussionCount; " discussion subjects"
    
    ' Show some statistics
    Dim totalReplies As Long = 0
    Dim i As Long
    For i = 1 To categoryCount
        totalReplies += categories(i).replyCount
    Next i
    
    Print "Total replies loaded: "; totalReplies
    Print "Memory usage: Approximately "; (categoryCount * 2); "KB"
    Print "Database loading complete!"
    Print ""
    
    Return 1  ' Success
    
ErrorHandler:
    Print "Error: Cannot open file "; filename
    'Print "Error details: " & Err & " - " & Error
    If fileNum > 0 Then Close #fileNum
    Return 0  ' Failure
End Function

    categories(categoryCount).keywords(0).text = "QUIT"
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(1).text = "EXIT"
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(2).text = "BYE"
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(3).text = "GOODBYE"
    categories(categoryCount).replyCount = 1
    categories(categoryCount).replies(0).text = "%"
    
    ' K_BLANK category
    categoryCount += 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywordCount = 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(0).text = "K_BLANK"
    categories(categoryCount).isFixed = 1
    categories(categoryCount).replyCount = 3
    categories(categoryCount).replies(0).text = "PLEASE WRITE SOMETHING, |"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(1).text = "DON'T JUST PRESS ENTER, TYPE SOMETHING PLEASE"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(2).text = "I'M WAITING FOR YOUR RESPONSE, |"
    
    ' K_REPEAT category
    categoryCount += 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywordCount = 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(0).text = "K_REPEAT"
    categories(categoryCount).isFixed = 1
    categories(categoryCount).replyCount = 3
    categories(categoryCount).replies(0).text = "DON'T REPEAT YOURSELF PLEASE"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(1).text = "YOU JUST SAID THAT"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(2).text = "PLEASE SAY SOMETHING DIFFERENT"
    
    ' K_IMPRP category
    categoryCount += 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywordCount = 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(0).text = "K_IMPRP"
    categories(categoryCount).isFixed = 1
    categories(categoryCount).replyCount = 3
    categories(categoryCount).replies(0).text = "PLEASE TYPE IN PROPER ENGLISH"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(1).text = "I CAN'T UNDERSTAND THE WAY YOU'RE REPLYING"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(2).text = "PLEASE WRITE MORE CLEARLY"
    
    ' KLast category (default responses)
    categoryCount += 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywordCount = 1
    categories(categoryCount).keywords(0).text = "KLast"
    categories(categoryCount).replyCount = 10
    categories(categoryCount).replies(0).text = "TELL ME MORE ABOUT THAT."
    categories(categoryCount).replies(1).text = "HOW DOES THAT MAKE YOU FEEL?"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(2).text = "WHAT DO YOU THINK ABOUT THAT?"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(3).text = "CAN YOU ELABORATE ON THAT?"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(4).text = "I SEE. PLEASE CONTINUE."
    categories(categoryCount).replies(5).text = "THAT'S INTERESTING. TELL ME MORE."
    categories(categoryCount).replies(6).text = "GO ON."
    categories(categoryCount).replies(7).text = "WHAT ELSE COMES TO MIND?"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(8).text = "CAN YOU GIVE ME AN EXAMPLE?"
    categories(categoryCount).replies(9).text = "HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT THAT?"
    
    ' Add some discussion subjects
    discussionCount = 5
    discussions(1) = "YOUR FAMILY"
    discussions(2) = "YOUR WORK"
    discussions(3) = "YOUR FEELINGS"
    discussions(4) = "YOUR DREAMS"
    discussions(5) = "YOUR PROBLEMS"
    
    Print "Built-in database created with "; categoryCount; " categories"
End Sub

' Improved flag condition evaluation
Function EvaluateCondition(catIndex As Long) As Long
    ' No condition means always true
    If categories(catIndex).ifCondition = "" Then Return 1
    
    Dim flagNum As Long = categories(catIndex).ifFlag
    Dim operatorStr As String = categories(catIndex).ifOperator
    Dim value As Long = categories(catIndex).ifValue
    
    ' Validate flag number
    If flagNum < 0 Or flagNum > 127 Then 
        Print "DEBUG: Invalid flag number " & flagNum & " in category " & catIndex
        Return 1
    End If
    
    Dim flagValue As Long = flags(flagNum).value
    
    Select Case operatorStr
        Case "="
            Return IIf(flagValue = value, 1, 0)
        Case "/"  ' Not equal
            Return IIf(flagValue <> value, 1, 0)
        Case "<"
            Return IIf(flagValue < value, 1, 0)
        Case ">"
            Return IIf(flagValue > value, 1, 0)
        Case Else
            Print "DEBUG: Unknown operator '" & operatorStr & "' in category " & catIndex
            Return 1
    End Select
End Function


' Fixed Main response generation engine - Matches ECC-ELIZA V4.09 specification exactly
Function GenerateResponse(userInput As String) As String
    Dim cleanedInput As String = CleanInput(userInput)
    Dim response As String = ""
    Dim i As Long, j As Long
    Dim reprocessCount As Long = 0
    Dim foundCategory As Long = 0
    Dim foundKeyword As String = ""
    
    Print "DEBUG: Processing input: '" & cleanedInput & "'"
    
    ' Handle special debug commands first
    If StringStartsWith(cleanedInput, "DFV ") And Len(cleanedInput) = 8 Then
        Dim flagNumStr As String = Mid(cleanedInput, 5, 3)
        Dim flagNum As Long = Val(flagNumStr)
        If flagNum >= 0 And flagNum <= 127 Then
            Return "Flag " + FormatNumber(flagNum, 3) + " = " + Str(flags(flagNum).value)
        Else
            Return "Invalid flag number. Use format: dFv 000 to dFv 127"
        End If
    End If
    
    ' Update conversation tracking
    conversationCount += 1
    
    ' Check for special input conditions FIRST (highest priority)
    If cleanedInput = "" Then
        blankCount += 1
        Return ProcessFixedCategory("K_BLANK")
    End If
    
    If IsRepeatedInput(cleanedInput) Then
        repeatCount += 1
        Return ProcessFixedCategory("K_REPEAT")
    End If
    
    If IsImproperInput(cleanedInput) Then
        Return ProcessFixedCategory("K_IMPRP")
    End If
    
    If Len(cleanedInput) < 10 And Int(Rnd * 100) < 40 Then
        Return ProcessFixedCategory("K_SHORT")
    End If
    
    If Len(cleanedInput) > 100 Then
        Return ProcessFixedCategory("K_LONG")
    End If

ProcessInput:
    reprocessCount += 1
    If reprocessCount > 3 Then
        Print "DEBUG: Max reprocessing reached, using KLast"
        GoTo UseKLast
    End If
    
    foundCategory = 0
    foundKeyword = ""
    
    Print "DEBUG: Scanning categories in priority order (attempt " & reprocessCount & ")"
    
    ' MAIN ALGORITHM: Process categories in FILE ORDER (priority order)
    For i = 1 To categoryCount
        ' Skip invalid categories
        If i < 1 Or i > MAX_CATEGORIES Then Continue For
        If categories(i).keywordCount <= 0 Then Continue For
        
        ' Skip fixed categories (handled separately)
        If categories(i).isFixed Then Continue For
        
        ' Skip KLast for now
        Dim isKLast As Long = 0
        If categories(i).keywordCount > 0 And categories(i).keywords(0).text = "KLast" Then
            isKLast = 1
            Continue For
        End If
        
        ' Check if condition allows this category
        If Not EvaluateCondition(i) Then 
            Print "DEBUG: Category " & i & " condition failed"
            Continue For
        End If
        
        ' Check each keyword in this category
        Dim keywordMatched As Long = 0
        Dim matchedKeywordText As String = ""
        
        For j = 0 To categories(i).keywordCount - 1
            If j < 0 Or j > UBound(categories(i).keywords) Then Continue For
            
            ' Test if keyword matches
            If KeywordMatches(categories(i).keywords(j), cleanedInput) Then
                keywordMatched = 1
                matchedKeywordText = categories(i).keywords(j).text
                Print "DEBUG: Keyword match found! Category " & i & ", keyword '" & matchedKeywordText & "'"
                Exit For
            End If
        Next j
        
        ' If no keyword matched in this category, continue to next category
        If Not keywordMatched Then Continue For
        
        ' We found a keyword match, but check probability
        Dim probabilityPassed As Long = 1
        If categories(i).probability < 100 Then
            Dim roll As Long = Int(Rnd * 100) + 1
            If roll > categories(i).probability Then
                Print "DEBUG: Category " & i & " probability check failed (" & categories(i).probability & "% vs " & roll & "%) - skipping"
                probabilityPassed = 0
            End If
        End If
        
        ' If probability check failed, continue searching (DON'T reprocess yet)
        If Not probabilityPassed Then Continue For
        
        ' SUCCESS: We found a matching category that passed all checks
        foundCategory = i
        foundKeyword = matchedKeywordText
        Exit For  ' Use first matching category (highest priority)
    Next i
    
    ' Handle _EXE categories - these can override normal categories
    For i = 1 To categoryCount
        If categories(i).isExecute And EvaluateCondition(i) Then
            Print "DEBUG: _EXE category " & i & " overriding normal selection"
            foundCategory = i
            foundKeyword = "_EXE"
            Exit For
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' If we found a category, use it
    If foundCategory > 0 Then
        Print "DEBUG: Using category " & foundCategory & " with keyword '" & foundKeyword & "'"
        
        ' Validate reply count
        If categories(foundCategory).replyCount <= 0 Then
            Print "DEBUG: Category has no replies, falling back to KLast"
            GoTo UseKLast
        End If
        
        ExecuteFlagCommands(foundCategory)
        Dim replyIndex As Long = GetNextReply(foundCategory)
        
        If replyIndex < 0 Or replyIndex >= categories(foundCategory).replyCount Then
            Print "DEBUG: Invalid reply index, falling back to KLast"
            GoTo UseKLast
        End If
        
        response = ProcessReply(categories(foundCategory).replies(replyIndex).text, cleanedInput, foundKeyword, categories(foundCategory).missingAsterisk)
        
        ' Track subject
        If categories(foundCategory).subject <> "" Then
            subjectCount += 1
            If subjectCount <= 100 Then subjects(subjectCount) = categories(foundCategory).subject
        End If
        
        ' Handle % exit command
        If categories(foundCategory).replies(replyIndex).exitType = 3 Then
            Print response
            Print "DO YOU REALLY WANT TO QUIT? (Y/N)"
            Dim quitResponse As String
            Input quitResponse
            If StringUpper(StringTrim(quitResponse)) = "Y" Or StringUpper(StringTrim(quitResponse)) = "YES" Then
                Return "GOODBYE " + userName + "! HAVE A NICE DAY!"
            Else
                Return "ALRIGHT, LET'S CONTINUE."
            End If
        End If
        
        UpdateReservedFlags()
        lastInput = cleanedInput
        Return response
    End If
    
    ' No category matched - check if we should reprocess
    ' ECC-ELIZA reprocesses 90% of the time when no match found due to probability skips
    Print "DEBUG: No category matched on attempt " & reprocessCount
    If reprocessCount = 1 And Int(Rnd * 100) < 90 Then
        Print "DEBUG: Reprocessing input (90% chance)..."
        GoTo ProcessInput
    End If

UseKLast:
    ' Use KLast as final fallback
    Print "DEBUG: Using KLast fallback"
    For i = 1 To categoryCount
        If categories(i).keywordCount > 0 And categories(i).keywords(0).text = "KLast" Then
            Print "DEBUG: Found KLast in category " & i
            ExecuteFlagCommands(i)
            Dim replyIndex As Long = GetNextReply(i)
            response = ProcessReply(categories(i).replies(replyIndex).text, cleanedInput, "KLast", categories(i).missingAsterisk)
            UpdateReservedFlags()
            lastInput = cleanedInput
            Return response
        End If
    Next i
    
    ' Final fallback if no KLast found
    Print "DEBUG: No KLast category found, using default response"
    UpdateReservedFlags()
    lastInput = cleanedInput
    Return "I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHAT YOU'RE SAYING."
End Function

' Get user name with validation
Sub GetUserName()
    Dim nameReply As String
    
    ' Use K_NAME category if available
    nameReply = ProcessFixedCategory("K_NAME")
    Print nameReply
    
    Do
        Line Input userName
        userName = StringUpper(StringTrim(userName))
        
        ' Remove non-alphabetic characters
        Dim cleanName As String = ""
        Dim i As Long
        For i = 1 To Len(userName)
            Dim c As String = Mid(userName, i, 1)
            If c >= "A" And c <= "Z" Then
                cleanName += c
            End If
        Next i
        
        userName = cleanName
        
        If userName <> "" And Len(userName) >= 2 Then Exit Do
        
        Print "PLEASE ENTER A VALID NAME:"
    Loop
End Sub

' Main chat loop
Sub MainChatLoop()
    Dim helloReply As String = ProcessFixedCategory("K_HELLO")
    Print helloReply
    Print "PLEASE TELL ME YOUR PROBLEMS."
    Print
    
    Dim userInput As String
    Do
        Print userName + "> ";
        Line Input userInput
        
        If userInput = "" Then
            Print "ELIZA> " + ProcessFixedCategory("K_BLANK")
            Print
            Continue Do
        End If
        
        Dim response As String = GenerateResponse(userInput)
        
        ' Handle quit responses
        If StringStartsWith(response, "GOODBYE") Or response = "QUIT" Then
            Print "ELIZA> " + response
            Exit Do
        End If
        
        Print "ELIZA> " + response
        Print
        
    Loop
End Sub

' Display program information
Sub ShowProgramInfo()
    Print "ECC-ELIZA Clone v4.2 for FreeBASIC/DOS"
    Print "======================================"
    Print "Based on the original ECC-ELIZA V4.09 specification"
    Print "Includes full DAT file parser and advanced flag system"
    Print "Fixed for large DAT files (up to " & MAX_CATEGORIES & " categories)"
    Print "NOTE: Loading 3000+ categories may take 1-2 minutes on older systems"
    Print
End Sub

' Main program entry point - Fixed logic
Sub Main()
    InitializeSystem()
    ShowProgramInfo()
    
    ' Try to load ELIZA.DAT file
    Print "Attempting to load ELIZA.DAT..."
    Dim loadResult As Long = LoadDataFile("ELIZA.DAT")
    
    If loadResult = 0 Then
        Print "ELIZA.DAT not found or failed to load, using built-in database"
        CreateBuiltInDatabase()
    Else
        Print "ELIZA.DAT loaded successfully!"
        Print "Ready to start conversation with full database."
    End If
    
    Print
    GetUserName()
    Print
    MainChatLoop()
End Sub

' Program starts here
Main()

# Define the folder containing the RDL files
$rdlFolder = "C:\Path\To\RDLFiles"

# Loop through all RDL files in the folder
Get-ChildItem -Path $rdlFolder -Filter *.rdl | ForEach-Object {
    $rdlFile = $_.FullName
    Write-Host "`nProcessing: $($_.Name)" -ForegroundColor Cyan

    try {
        # Load the XML content
        [xml]$xml = Get-Content $rdlFile

        # Extract metadata
        $reportName = $_.BaseName
        $description = $xml.Report.Description
        $dataSources = $xml.Report.DataSources.DataSource.Name
        $datasets = $xml.Report.DataSets.DataSet.Name
        $parameters = $xml.Report.ReportParameters.ReportParameter | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }

        # Display extracted metadata
        Write-Host "Report Name     : $reportName"
        Write-Host "Description     : $description"
        Write-Host "Data Sources    : $($dataSources -join ', ')"
        Write-Host "Datasets        : $($datasets -join ', ')"
        Write-Host "Report Parameters: $($parameters -join ', ')"
    }
    catch {
        Write-Host "Failed to parse $rdlFile" -ForegroundColor Red
        Write-Host $_.Exception.Message
    }
}

import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import messagebox, Scrollbar, Listbox, Entry, Label, Button, Frame, Toplevel, StringVar, END, BOTH, LEFT, RIGHT, X, Y, TOP, W, E, S
from pypinyin import Style
import pypinyin
import webbrowser
import json
#================ADD-IMAGE-ICON=================
import os
import sys

def resource_path(relative_path):
    """ Get the absolute path to the resource, works for PyInstaller. """
    if getattr(sys, '_MEIPASS', False):
        return os.path.join(sys._MEIPASS, relative_path)
    return os.path.join(os.path.abspath("."), relative_path)

# Use this function to load files:
splash_image = resource_path("splash-1.png")
icon_path = resource_path("opentool.ico")
#================ADD-IMAGE-ICON=================
# ==================ADD-SPLASH==================
import tkinter as tk
from PIL import Image, ImageTk
import time


def show_splash(image_path):
    # Create splash screen window
    splash = tk.Tk()
    splash.overrideredirect(True)  # Remove window border
    
    # Load the image
    image = Image.open(image_path)
    img = ImageTk.PhotoImage(image)

    # Get image dimensions
    img_width, img_height = image.size

    # Calculate position to center the splash screen
    screen_width = splash.winfo_screenwidth()
    screen_height = splash.winfo_screenheight()
    x = (screen_width - img_width) // 2
    y = (screen_height - img_height) // 2
    splash.geometry(f"{img_width}x{img_height}+{x}+{y}")

    # Set transparent background
    splash.config(bg="white")
    splash.attributes("-transparentcolor", "white")  # Make white color transparent

    # Display the image
    label = tk.Label(splash, image=img, bg="white")
    label.pack()

    # Display the splash screen for 5 seconds
    splash.after(5000, splash.destroy)
    splash.mainloop()


# Call splash screen function
show_splash(splash_image) # Replace with your image file path 1 To 6

# ==================ADD-SPLASH==================
FONT_1 = ('Microsoft YaHei', 14, 'normal')
FONT_2 = ('Arial', 12, 'normal')


# Popup window for Add/Edit
class PopupDialog(tk.Toplevel):
    def __init__(self, parent, existing_name=None, existing_url=None):
        super().__init__()
        sw = self.winfo_screenwidth()
        sh = self.winfo_screenheight() - 100
        ww = 400
        wh = 110
        x = (sw - ww) / 2
        y = (sh - wh) / 2
        self.geometry("%dx%d+%d+%d" % (ww, wh, x, y))
        self.resizable(0, 0)

        self.title('Edit Path' if existing_name else 'Add Path')
        self.transient(parent)
        self.parent = parent
        frame = Frame(self)
        frame.grid()

        self.grab_set()
        self.protocol("WM_DELETE_WINDOW", self.cancel)

        self.name = StringVar(value=existing_name if existing_name else "")
        self.url = StringVar(value=existing_url if existing_url else "")
        self.existing_name = existing_name

        # Row 1: Name
        Label(frame, text='Name:').grid(row=0, column=0, sticky=E, pady=8)
        self.entry1 = Entry(frame, textvariable=self.name, width=50)
        self.entry1.grid(row=0, column=1, columnspan=4, sticky=W, pady=8)

        # Row 2: Path
        Label(frame, text='Path:').grid(row=1, column=0, sticky=E)
        Entry(frame, textvariable=self.url, width=50).grid(row=1, column=1, columnspan=4, sticky=W)

        # Row 3: Buttons
        Button(frame, text="OK", command=self.ok).grid(row=2, column=2, sticky=S, pady=10)
        Button(frame, text="Cancel", command=self.cancel).grid(row=2, column=3, sticky=S, pady=10)

        self.entry1.focus_set()
        self.bind("<Return>", self.ok)
        self.bind("<Escape>", self.cancel)

    def ok(self, event=None):
        new_name = self.name.get().strip()
        new_url = self.url.get().strip()

        if not new_name or not new_url:
            messagebox.showwarning('Warning', 'Input cannot be empty!')
            return

        if self.existing_name and new_name != self.existing_name:
            if new_name in self.parent.urllist:
                if not messagebox.askyesno('Prompt', f'Name ‚Äú{new_name}‚Äù already exists. Overwrite it?'):
                    return
            del self.parent.urllist[self.existing_name]

        self.parent.urllist[new_name] = new_url

        self.parent.listbox.delete(0, END)
        for item in self.parent.urllist:
            self.parent.listbox.insert(END, item)
        self.destroy()

    def cancel(self, event=None):
        self.destroy()


# Main application window
class Application(tk.Frame):
    def __init__(self, master=None):
        super().__init__()
        self.master = master
        self.pack()

        self.urllist = self.readUrlList()
        if self.urllist:
            self.createWidgets()
            self.mainloop()
        else:
            messagebox.showinfo('Error', 'Failed to load URL list! Please check if openlist.json exists and is formatted correctly.')

    def readUrlList(self):
        try:
            with open('openlist.json', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f_obj:
                return json.load(f_obj)
        except FileNotFoundError:
            return {}

    def saveUrllist(self):
        with open('openlist.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
            json.dump(self.urllist, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)
        print('File saved successfully.')

    def createWidgets(self):
        # Search bar
        self.frame1 = Frame()
        self.frame1.pack(side=TOP, fill=X)
        Label(self.frame1, text='Search:', font=FONT_2).pack(side=LEFT)
        self.keywdbox = Entry(self.frame1, font=FONT_2)
        self.keywdbox.pack(side=LEFT, fill=X, expand=True)
        self.keywdbox.focus_set()

        # List box with scrollbar
        self.frame2 = Frame()
        self.frame2.pack(side=TOP, fill=X, pady=5)
        self.scrolly = Scrollbar(self.frame2)
        self.scrolly.pack(side=RIGHT, fill=Y)
        self.listbox = Listbox(self.frame2, width=60, height=15, font=FONT_1, yscrollcommand=self.scrolly.set)
        self.listbox.pack(fill=BOTH, expand=True)
        self.scrolly.config(command=self.listbox.yview)

        # Button controls
        self.frame3 = Frame(root, bg="#2c3e50")
        self.frame3.pack(side=TOP, fill=BOTH, pady=10)
        #Label(self.frame3, width=10).pack(side=LEFT)
        Button(self.frame3, text='Add', width=10, command=self.additem).pack(side=LEFT, padx=10)
        Button(self.frame3, text='Edit', width=10, command=self.edititem).pack(side=LEFT, padx=10)
        Button(self.frame3, text='Delete', width=10, command=self.deleteitem).pack(side=LEFT, padx=10)
        #Label(self.frame3, width=10).pack(side=RIGHT)

        # Populate list
        for item in self.urllist:
            self.listbox.insert(END, item)

        self.doevent()

    def doevent(self):
        self.keywdbox.bind("<KeyRelease>", self.showlist)
        self.listbox.bind('<Double-Button-1>', self.openurl)
        self.listbox.bind('<Return>', self.openurl)
        self.listbox.bind('<Left>', lambda e: self.keywdbox.focus_set())
        self.keywdbox.bind("<Down>", self.jump_to_listbox)

    def additem(self):
        pw = PopupDialog(self)
        self.wait_window(pw)
        self.saveUrllist()

    def edititem(self):
        index = self.listbox.curselection()
        if not index:
            messagebox.showinfo('Info', 'Please select an item to edit!')
            return

        name = self.listbox.get(index)
        url = self.urllist.get(name, "")
        pw = PopupDialog(self, existing_name=name, existing_url=url)
        self.wait_window(pw)
        self.saveUrllist()

    def deleteitem(self):
        index = self.listbox.curselection()
        if not index:
            messagebox.showinfo('Info', 'Please select an item to delete!')
            return

        item = self.listbox.get(index)
        if messagebox.askyesno('Delete', f'Delete {item}?'):
            self.listbox.delete(index)
            del self.urllist[item]
            self.saveUrllist()
            messagebox.showinfo('Info', 'Deleted successfully')

    def openurl(self, event):
        index = self.listbox.curselection()
        if not index:
            return
        urlname = self.listbox.get(index)
        url = self.urllist.get(urlname)
        if url:
            webbrowser.open(url)
        else:
            messagebox.showinfo('Error', 'Failed to open. URL is empty.')

    def jump_to_listbox(self, event):
        if self.listbox.size():
            self.listbox.select_clear(0, END)
            self.listbox.select_set(0)
            self.listbox.activate(0)
            self.listbox.focus_set()

    def showlist(self, event):
        keywd = self.keywdbox.get().strip()
        self.listbox.delete(0, END)
        if keywd:
            for item in self.urllist:
                cond_1 = keywd.lower() in item.lower()
                cond_2 = keywd.lower() in pypinyin.slug(item.lower(), separator='')
                cond_3 = keywd.lower() in pypinyin.slug(item.lower(), style=Style.FIRST_LETTER, separator='')
                if any([cond_1, cond_2, cond_3]):
                    self.listbox.insert(END, item)
        else:
            for item in self.urllist:
                self.listbox.insert(END, item)


if __name__ == '__main__':
    root = tk.Tk()
    root.title('Najeeb Shah Khan Open Everything')
    root.configure(bg="#2c3e50")
    
    try:
        root.iconbitmap(icon_path)
    except:
        pass
    root.resizable(0, 0)
    app = Application(master=root)
    if app.urllist:
        app.saveUrllist()
